nerated test classpath.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.springframework.ai:spring-ai-autoconfigure-model-tool:2.0.0\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"Provides tool-calling auto-configuration and related beans needed to exercise the target auto-configuration's tool-calling branch; it is also an optional companion module.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-autoconfigure:4.1.0\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"The target artifact is a Spring Boot auto-configuration module and its configuration classes depend on Spring Boot auto-configuration APIs.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-test:4.1.0\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"ApplicationContextRunner is the normal lightweight way to exercise Spring Boot auto-configuration without starting an application or external services.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No Docker image, environment variable, API key, or system property is required. Use local Spring Boot ApplicationContextRunner-style tests with stub ChatModel/local beans rather than a real model provider. For Spring AI 2.0.0, do not use the removed spring.ai.chat.client.tool-calling.stream-tool-call-responses property or ChatClientBuilderProperties.ToolCalling.isStreamToolCallResponses(); the 2.0.0 ToolCalling properties expose enabled and advisorOrder.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The existing RC2 test fails to compile against 2.0.0 because it asserts an API/property removed before the final release.\",\n    \"Because the target artifact declares important collaborators as optional, a plain generated scaffold may compile poorly or only cover metadata/resource loading rather than the actual auto-configuration behavior.\",\n    \"Keep Spring AI companion dependencies aligned to 2.0.0 and Spring Boot dependencies aligned to 4.1.0 to avoid mixed RC/final API drift.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_09060562aa11a85f016a403d9271588190b2f4bf0274d43c90\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1705, "output": 1592, "cacheRead": 20480, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 23777, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782594949249, "responseId": "resp_09060562aa11a85f016a403d85c05081909a338211c2a57fb8"}}
